OL,6,F"Your husband was entitled to feel
OL,7,Fsafe and secure in his home and in the
OL,8,Fcompany of his wife."
OL,10,FThornton's husband would suffer abuse
OL,11,Fand attacks "almost night after
OL,12,Fnight", the court was told.
OL,14,FOn one occasion, in 2018, the police
OL,15,Fwere called about an assault but they
OL,16,Fdeclined to pursue the matter.
OL,18,F"You caused injuries on many occasions
OL,19,Fand made his life a misery," Judge
OL,20,FThackray told Thornton.
