OL,6,F"He was very much in love with you for
OL,7,Fa long time but you abused that love
OL,8,Fin a most grotesque way night after
OL,9,Fnight. You abused and assaulted your
OL,10,Fhusband, who did his best to love and
OL,11,Fsupport you in every way possible."
OL,13,FThornton, who had been in custody at
OL,14,FNew Hall Prison, near Wakefield, was
OL,15,Fjailed for two years and given a 10-
OL,16,Fyear restraining order.
OL,18,FAfter the hearing, Thornton's husband
OL,19,Ftold the Grimsby Live website: "I just
OL,20,Fdon't want her to hurt anyone else."
